    narr:generatedFrom "7d2f2e518105a6de14673f053f2b231f1723885d" ;
    narr:narration """This hub catalogs the evolving lexicon and rhetorical architecture of Aswritten, serving as a recognition surface for the company's self-positioning. The core narrative trajectory moves from enterprise-focused framing toward [the hallucination question](narr:Obs_KeyPhrase_Hallucinating) and [context engineering](narr:Obs_KeyPhrase_ContextEngineering) as primary hooks. Foundational positioning relies on the [narrative as steering vector](narr:Obs_KeyPhrase_SteeringVector) thesis, supported by [worldview as code](narr:Obs_KeyPhrase_WorldviewAsCode) and the promise to [think like your org](narr:Obs_KeyPhrase_ThinkLikeYourOrg). 

Voice-level observations document a distinct idiolect characterized by [archery metaphors](narr:StyleObs_5), [Clojure-framed architectural logic](narr:StyleObs_ClojureIdiolect), and a reliance on [antithetical reframe constructions](narr:StyleObs_VerbatimReframe). Product-specific terminology—such as [lens drafting](narr:StyleObs_LensDraftingTerm), [micro-telltales](narr:StyleObs_LensMicroTelltale), and [collective memory](narr:Observation_KeyPhrases_1)—recur as load-bearing identifiers. The documentation also captures the tension between [testing vs. selling](narr:StyleObs_TestingVsSelling) and the shift from [information to perspective](narr:Obs_InformationVsPerspective), surfacing the company's internal struggle to define its product identity against industry-standard semantic layers.""" ;
